  "prompt": "What will be my rank I scored 325 in neet?",
  "response": "Your rank in NEET depends on several factors, including the total number of candidates, the difficulty level of the exam, and the performance of other candidates. However, based on previous years' trends:\n\n- A score of **325** in NEET is generally considered **low** compared to the cut-off marks for government medical colleges (which are usually much higher, often above 550-600).\n- Your rank could be in the **lakhs** (e.g., 100,000+), depending on how many candidates scored higher than you.\n\nFor a more accurate prediction, you can use NEET rank predictors available online or wait for the official results and rank list from NTA. If you're aiming for government or private medical colleges, you may need to consider other options like state quotas, private colleges, or management seats, or prepare for improvement if you plan to retake NEET.",
